SUMMARY:AI Infrastructure That Scales: Foundations for Real-World Deployme
 nt
DESCRIPTION:Data Science Raleigh\nExperimentation is easy. Real-world depl
 oyment? That’s where the infrastructure proves its worth.\n\nIn this ses
 sion\, we’ll go beyond prototypes and pilot programs to explore what it 
 really takes to build AI infrastructure that holds up under production dem
 ands. From GPU scheduling and model orchestration to observability\, gover
 nance\, and scaling compute across hybrid environments—this discussion i
 s for teams ready to move past the lab and into sustained delivery.\n\nOur
  panel of leaders will break down architectural trade-offs\, emerging best
  practices\, and the organizational realities of supporting production-gra
 de AI.\n\n**What You'll Learn:**\n\n1️⃣ **Foundational Stack Component
 s:** What your AI infrastructure needs to support scale\, speed\, and stab
 ility in production.\n\n2️⃣ **Deployment Realities:** Insights into la
 tency\, availability\, compliance\, and lifecycle management when shipping
  AI to production.\n\n3️⃣**Infrastructure as Collaboration:** How infr
 a\, ML\, and product teams can align on goals\, budgets\, and tooling with
 out bottlenecks.Engage live with founders and builders shaping the future 
 of autonomous enterprise solutions.\n\nPanelists to be announced soon.\n\n
 **[Register here](https://hubs.ly/Q03VWZMN0)**
