SUMMARY:The Context Layer: The Emerging Stack for Context-Aware AI
DESCRIPTION:Data Science Raleigh\nAs enterprises push AI into production\,
  context isn’t a luxury—it’s a requirement. Whether you're mitigatin
 g hallucinations\, aligning responses with brand and policy guidelines\, o
 r ensuring traceable\, compliant outcomes\, context-aware architecture is 
 becoming foundational to trustworthy AI.\n\nThis webinar explores the “c
 ontext layer”—the emerging stack of tools\, techniques\, and workflows
  that inject dynamic\, domain-specific intelligence into AI systems. We’
 ll examine how leading teams are designing for retrieval-augmented generat
 ion (RAG)\, grounding\, memory\, and orchestration to ensure outputs refle
 ct the right data\, tone\, and constraints at the right time.\n\n**What Yo
 u'll Learn:**\n\n1️⃣ **Architecting the Context Layer:** What the emer
 ging stack looks like—from vector databases and memory systems to orches
 tration layers and policy enforcement.\n\n2️⃣ **Reducing Hallucination
 s:** How context-aware design helps constrain generative outputs to known\
 , verifiable sources.\n\n3️⃣ **Boosting Trust & Alignment:** Technique
 s for integrating domain-specific knowledge\, tone\, and compliance rules 
 directly into AI interactions.\n\n4️⃣ **From Static to Dynamic Context
 :** When to use retrieval\, when to use memory\, and how to balance both f
 or adaptive\, scalable systems.\n\n**[Register here](https://hubs.ly/Q042c
 LJx0)**
